.Dd June 20, 2026
.Dt CLODE 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm clode
.Nd run the latest Claude Code under host Node, no Bun runtime
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl -clode-verbose
.Op Ar claude-args ...
.Nm
.Cm update
.Op Cm stable | latest | Ar version
.Nm
.Fl -clode-help
.Nm
.Fl -clode-version
.Nm
.Fl -clode-watch
.Nm
.Fl -clode-internal-update
.Op Ar channel
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
locates an upstream
.Xr claude 1
binary (from a provider package or your own install), extracts its JavaScript
bundle once, caches it per binary under your cache directory, and runs it under
the system Node.
A changed provider binary re-extracts on next launch, so updates are
transparent.
.Nm
never installs, names, or replaces anything called
.Ar claude ;
it reads the upstream binary only as the source of the bundle and never
redistributes it.
.Pp
.Fl -clode-version
prints clode's own version and exits, and
.Fl -clode-help
prints clode's own options and exits.
All other arguments pass through to Claude Code.
.Pp
By default
.Nm
emits nothing of its own \(em only Claude Code's output \(em so it is a
transparent stand-in.
.Fl -clode-verbose
(or
.Ev CLODE_VERBOSE Ns = Ns Cm 1 )
un-mutes clode's own progress, such as bundle extraction and dependency
installation.
The flag may appear in any position and is consumed by
.Nm ;
it is never passed through to Claude Code.
Errors are always shown regardless.
.Pp
.Nm update
.Op Cm stable | latest | Ar version
fetches the latest upstream Claude Code host-agnostically (a fixed
.Cm linux-x64
build \(em the embedded JavaScript is the same on every platform) into clode's
provider store and verifies its checksum; the next launch extracts and runs it.
The default channel is
.Cm stable .
.Pp
.Nm
patches Claude Code's in-app auto-updater to run
.Nm Fl -clode-internal-update
.Op Ar channel ,
a non-interactive form of
.Nm update ,
so the in-TUI
.Ic claude update
affordance (and the automatic updater) fetch via clode rather than the npm path
that cannot apply under clode; the bundle's
.Dq Update installed \(em Restart to apply
message then means relaunch to run the freshly fetched version.
You normally invoke
.Nm update
directly rather than
.Fl -clode-internal-update .
.Pp
.Fl -clode-watch
runs one update-signal check (is a newer Claude Code available, and does its
changelog carry signals that bear on running under Node?), prints a summary, and
exits.
A normal launch also performs this check opportunistically, at most once per day,
fully in the background, and prints a one-line notice on the next launch only when
a newer version carries such signals.
.Pp
.Nm
itself is a Node program
.Pq Li #!/usr/bin/env node ,
so it needs
.Xr node 1
on
.Ev PATH
to start.
An ES5-safe prologue prints a friendly
.Dq node too old
message on an outdated node; a truly missing node yields
.Li "env: node: not found" .
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width CLODE_VERSION_DIR
.It Ev CLODE_VERBOSE
When non-empty, un-mutes clode's own progress output (same as
.Fl -clode-verbose ) .
.It Ev CLODE_CLAUDE_BIN
Absolute path to the upstream claude binary (highest precedence).
.It Ev CLODE_VERSION_DIR
A specific on-disk version path to run.
.It Ev CLODE_PROVIDERS
Store for binaries fetched by
.Nm update
(default
.Pa ${XDG_DATA_HOME:-$HOME/.local/share}/clode/providers ) .
.It Ev CLODE_RELEASES_URL
Base URL for
.Nm update
downloads.
.It Ev CLODE_FETCH_PLATFORM
Which platform's build
.Nm update
fetches (default
.Cm linux-x64 ) .
.It Ev CLODE_NO_WATCH
If set, disable the opportunistic on-launch update-signal check.
.It Ev CLODE_WATCH_INTERVAL
Seconds between opportunistic checks (default 86400).
.It Ev CLODE_WATCH_DIR
Directory for watcher state (throttle + notice); default
.Pa ${XDG_CACHE_HOME:-$HOME/.cache}/clode .
.It Ev CLODE_CACHE
Cache root (default
.Pa ${XDG_CACHE_HOME:-$HOME/.cache}/clode ) .
.It Ev CLODE_LIBEXEC
Directory holding the extractor and Bun shim.
.It Ev CLODE_NODE
Host node (absolute path).
.It Ev CLODE_PATH
Clean-env PATH for the launched process.
.It Ev DISABLE_INSTALLATION_CHECKS
Set to 0 to re-enable the upstream npm-deprecation notices (default 1).
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Pa LIBEXEC/extract-claude-js.cjs , Pa LIBEXEC/bun-shim.cjs
Extractor and Bun-global shim.
.It Pa ${XDG_CACHE_HOME:-$HOME/.cache}/clode/<key>/cli.cjs
Per-binary extracted bundle cache.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr claude 1 ,
.Xr node 1
.Sh AUTHORS
.An Amitai Schleier
